---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Snip URL Shortener"
  description="Snip is a free, fast and privacy-friendly URL shortener with built-in click analytics, running on Cloudflare's edge network."
>
  <article class="prose-snip mx-auto max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">About Snip</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-ink-muted">
      Snip is a free URL shortener built for speed and simplicity. Paste any
      long link, get a short one back, and share it anywhere. Every link comes
      with built-in analytics so you can see exactly how it performs.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">How it works</h2>
    <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-5 text-ink-muted">
      <li>Paste a long URL on the home page and click <em>Shorten URL</em>.</li>
      <li>Share the short link — it redirects instantly from the edge.</li>
      <li>
        Open the <a class="text-clay-500 underline" href="/stats">Statistics</a>
        page and enter your code to see clicks, trends and sources.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Built on Cloudflare</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-muted">
      Snip runs on Cloudflare Pages with a D1 database, so redirects resolve in
      milliseconds from data centres around the world. The interface is built
      with Astro for fast, SEO-friendly pages.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
